                    <img style="height: 163px" class="rounded-2 d-block mx-auto" src="./images/clients/cactus-flower.svg" alt="Cactus Flower Apps Logo">

                    <p class="card-text mt-3">In what became a contract-to-hire position, I spent a year collaborating one-on-one with another entrepreneur, gaining valuable experience in product delivery. </p>
                    <p>One key lesson I learned is the importance of structuring project resources from the start. By consolidating all assets within a dedicated Google Account, every tool, document, and integration remains centralized—making it easy to transfer ownership to the client when needed.</p>
                    <p>
                        Other experiences included a deep dive into Google Apps Script (GAS), which became a defining moment for me and my client. We immediately clicked, knowing this would be a great collaboration. The GAS library serves as a gateway to powerful automation tools, turning any Gmail account into a central hub for streamlining business workflows.
                    </p>

                    @* <a asp-area="" asp-controller="projects" asp-action="projects" asp-route-id="beth-owen-watercolors"> *@
