        <div class="project-card col-md-6 col-12 mb-4">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <img style="" class="w-100 rounded-2 d-block mx-auto" src="./images/clients/art-website-preview-2.svg" alt="Beth Owen Watercolors">
                    <a class="text-center d-block" href="https://bethowenwatercolors.com/" target="_blank">www.bethowenwatercolors.com</a>
                    <p class="card-text mt-3">This "ArtStore" website is the first of its kind. I built it with a custom CMS that I designed as a no-code solution for building websites.</p>
                    <p>The code I write empowers my clients with creative freedom.</p>
                    <p>This solution gives the client complete control over customizing their website, even after I deliver the final product. They used it to build an art website, but it can be used to create any website that requires a similar storefront.</p>
                    <p>One of the key requirements for this project was that I wouldn't need to step in later to update content, create new pages, rearrange sections, add images, etc. These are all features the client can manage independently through built-in editors.</p>
                    <p>Another advantage of this project—one that you can benefit from—is that I designed it to be plug-and-play, making it easy to spin up new websites quickly.</p>
                    <a asp-area="" asp-controller="projects" asp-action="projects" asp-route-id="beth-owen-watercolors">
                        <button class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm mx-auto d-block">Take a Look</button>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

